article.headline: Hofstra 38, William &amp, Mary 14
article.story: HEMPSTEAD, N.Y. (AP) -- Bryan Savage accounted for five touchdowns and Hofstra routed William & Mary 38-14 on Saturday. Savage had 13 carries for 57 yards and three TDs. He also completed 15 of 17 passes for 196 yards and two more touchdowns for the Pride (7-2, 4-2 Colonial Athletic Association). Savage scored on a 12-yard run with 8:25 left in the first to tie it at 7. He tossed a 6-yard TD pass to Charles Sullivan and went in from the 1 to help Hofstra take a 21-7 lead into the second quarter. Savage tossed a 12-yard scoring strike to Ottis Lewis in the second and ran 11 yards for a TD in the third. Terrence Riggins had a 2-yard TD run and Mike Potts had a 16-yard touchdown pass for the Tribe (4-5, 2-3).
